<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="190" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1275,172,557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">ETYMOLOGY. — This species is dedicated to the Italian amphipodologist Sandro Ruffo, for his friendship and tireless work on amphipods.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="190" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1275,172,557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">DIAGNOSIS. — Cephalic lobe rounded. Pereon segments 5-7 and pleon segments 1-3 smooth. Urosomite 1 with</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1275,172,557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">a small dorsal tooth. Gnathopods 1-2,carpus longer than propodus; palm strongly oblique and dentate; dactylus with a long antero-distal setae. Coxa 4 deeply excavate posteriorly. Outer ramus of uropod 3 with distal article about 1/13 of proximal article. Telson cleft to about 6/7 of its length.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1247,618,1669]" box="[714,859,618,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1247,618,1669]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
Female (
<quantity box="[801,880,650,677]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
). Lateral cephalic lobe rounded, eyes lacking (
<figureCitation box="[813,936,682,709]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). Antenna 1, with callynophore; flagellum with 30+ articles; accessory flagellum with 5 articles. Upper lip rounded and apically setose (
<figureCitation box="[894,987,779,805]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Lower lip (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1233,779,805]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
), outer lobe elongate, with facial and distal setae; mandibular lobe well developed. Mandible (
<figureCitation box="[722,840,874,901]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 2E, F</figureCitation>
), incisor toothed; molar triturative; left lacinia mobilis large, with many teeth. Maxilla 1 (
<figureCitation box="[849,989,938,965]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 2G, H</figureCitation>
), inner plate densely setose; outer plate with 11 spines at distal end; distal margin of palp article 2 with stout short spines and a row of submarginal setae. Maxilla 2, inner and outer plates densely setose; inner plate with row of facial setae. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1233,1099,1125]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[213,1174,222,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[201,1194,193,1571]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, maxilliped; B, gnathopod 1; C, palm of gnathopod 1; D, gnathopod 2; E, palm of gnathopod 2; A, D, E, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, C, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E, 0.2 mm; D, 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757309/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), inner plate with 3 short and stout apical spines; outer plate inner margin with a row of short and stout spines, longer spines apically; palp articles 2-3 with long facial and distal setae, article 4 with long distal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1247,618,1669]" lastBlockId="7.[151,684,1034,1669]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
Coxa 1 short and triangular, distal margin with small setae (
<figureCitation box="[853,942,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[213,1174,222,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[201,1194,193,1571]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, maxilliped; B, gnathopod 1; C, palm of gnathopod 1; D, gnathopod 2; E, palm of gnathopod 2; A, D, E, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, C, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E, 0.2 mm; D, 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757309/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Coxa 2 rectangular, postero-distal margin with 4 setae (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1148,1355,1381]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[213,1174,222,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[201,1194,193,1571]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, maxilliped; B, gnathopod 1; C, palm of gnathopod 1; D, gnathopod 2; E, palm of gnathopod 2; A, D, E, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, C, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E, 0.2 mm; D, 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757309/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Coxa 3 rectangular. Coxa 4 deeply excavate posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[722,809,1419,1445]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Gnathopod 1 (
<figureCitation box="[992,1111,1419,1445]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[213,1174,222,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[201,1194,193,1571]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, maxilliped; B, gnathopod 1; C, palm of gnathopod 1; D, gnathopod 2; E, palm of gnathopod 2; A, D, E, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, C, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E, 0.2 mm; D, 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757309/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 3B, C</figureCitation>
), basis anterior margin with sparse setae, posterior margin with a group of medial setae; merus, carpus and propodus densely setose posteriorly; carpus 1/4 longer than propodus; palm strongly oblique and dentate; dactylus fitting palm, bearing a long antero-distal seta. Gnathopod 2 (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1233,1610,1637]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[213,1174,222,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[201,1194,193,1571]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, maxilliped; B, gnathopod 1; C, palm of gnathopod 1; D, gnathopod 2; E, palm of gnathopod 2; A, D, E, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, C, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E, 0.2 mm; D, 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757309/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 3D, E</figureCitation>
), basis with sparse setae; carpus 1/3 longer than propodus; carpus and propodus bearing several rows of long setae and two sequences of tiny setae posteriorly; palm strongly oblique, dentate; dactylus with a proximal and a long antero-distal seta, not fitting palm. Basis of pereopod 7 lobate posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[294,388,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[151,162,1631,1648]" captionTargetBox="[282,1132,230,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[268,1127,219,1618]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp., holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); A, pereopod 7; B, uropod 1; C, uropod 2; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B-E, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757311/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Epimera 2-3 produced. Urosomite 1 with a small dorsal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[585,672,1227,1253]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1223,174,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1245,164,1599]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp.; A, habitus; B, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2; C, upper lip; D, lower lip; E, right mandible; F, incisor and lacinia mobilis of left mandible; G, H, maxilla 1; A, C-H, holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); B, paratype, 25.3 mm (MNRJ 15698). Scale bars: A, C-E, G, 0.5 mm; B, 1.0 mm; F, 0.2 mm; H, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757307/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Uropod 1 (
<figureCitation box="[273,357,1259,1285]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[151,162,1631,1648]" captionTargetBox="[282,1132,230,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[268,1127,219,1618]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp., holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); A, pereopod 7; B, uropod 1; C, uropod 2; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B-E, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757311/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
), peduncle with a disto-lateral process tipped with a stout spine; rami as long as peduncle. Uropod 2 (
<figureCitation box="[415,513,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[151,162,1631,1648]" captionTargetBox="[282,1132,230,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[268,1127,219,1618]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp., holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); A, pereopod 7; B, uropod 1; C, uropod 2; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B-E, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757311/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), inner ramus longer than peduncle; outer ramus broken. Uropod 3 (
<figureCitation box="[274,363,1387,1413]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[151,162,1631,1648]" captionTargetBox="[282,1132,230,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[268,1127,219,1618]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp., holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); A, pereopod 7; B, uropod 1; C, uropod 2; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B-E, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757311/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
), inner ramus slightly shorter than outer ramus, with 6 proximal plumose setae on proximal inner margin; outer ramus twice the length of peduncle, distal article about 1/13 of proximal article. Telson (
<figureCitation box="[428,512,1515,1541]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[151,162,1631,1648]" captionTargetBox="[282,1132,230,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[268,1127,219,1618]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Valettiopsis ruffoi n. sp., holotype, 25 mm (MNRJ 15697); A, pereopod 7; B, uropod 1; C, uropod 2; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B-E, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757311/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) deeply cleft to about 6/7 of its length.
</paragraph>
