<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[714,1247,1034,1477]" box="[714,814,1034,1060]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[714,1247,1034,1477]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
<taxonomicName authority="Serejo &amp; Wakabara, 2003" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Wakabara" authorityYear="2003" box="[714,895,1065,1093]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruffoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[714,895,1065,1093]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Valettiopsis ruffoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[903,964,1066,1092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmes" authorityYear="1908" box="[1107,1217,1066,1093]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis box="[1107,1217,1066,1093]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">V. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having slender gnathopods 1-2 with the carpus distinctly longer than propodus. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Serejo &amp; Wakabara, 2003" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Wakabara" authorityYear="2003" box="[714,802,1161,1187]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruffoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[714,802,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">V. ruffoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,870,1162,1188]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmes" authorityYear="1908" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">V. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1909" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrodactyla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">V. macrodactyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnard" authorityYear="1961" box="[859,1045,1226,1253]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multidentata">
<emphasis box="[859,1045,1226,1253]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">V. multidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the strongly oblique palm on gnathopods 1-2, which are nearly transverse in the other species; coxa 4 deeply excavated posteriorly; pereopod 7 basis lobate postero-distally, not tapering; reduced tooth on urosomite 1; and outer ramus of uropod 3 with distal article very short, about 1/13 of proximal article.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[714,1048,1547,1573]" box="[714,1048,1547,1573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">DISTRIBUTIONAL NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[714,1247,1611,1669]" lastBlockId="8.[714,1247,170,485]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">
Knowledge of the geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmes" authorityYear="1908" box="[714,834,1643,1669]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,834,1643,1669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Valettiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[852,920,1643,1669]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="7.[151,162,931,948]" captionTargetBox="[154,1241,175,891]" captionTargetId="figure-281@7.[153,1242,173,901]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIG. 5. — Distribution of the genus Valettiopsis Holmes, 1908;, V. multidentata Barnard, 1961;, V. ruffoi n. sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="194">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) is poor, because the species are found mostly in moderate to great ocean depths and have been captured only rarely. Two species have been recorded in the Atlantic Ocean: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1909" box="[238,409,266,293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrodactyla">
<emphasis box="[238,409,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="195">V. macrodactyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Serejo &amp; Wakabara, 2003" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Wakabara" authorityYear="2003" box="[466,558,265,291]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruffoi" status="n. sp.">
